The proof of `not_of_mem_construction_omega` is incomplete (it has `sorry`). This lemma states that if `φ` satisfies certain conditions, then `φ ∉ U`.
We need to complete this lemma first.

Let's complete `not_of_mem_construction_omega`.
The goal is `φ ∉ construction_omega T hT`.
The proof is by contradiction. Assume `φ ∈ construction_omega T hT`.
This means `φ ∈ construction T hT i` for some `i`.
If `i = 0`, then `φ ∈ { δ | χ ➝ δ ∈ T.theory }`, so `χ ➝ φ ∈ T.theory`.
If `i > 0`, then `φ ∈ construction T hT i`.
Looking at the structure of `construction T hT i`:
- If `i = 0`, `φ ∈ { δ | χ ➝ δ ∈ T.theory }` means `χ ➝ φ ∈ T.theory`.
- If `i > 0`, then `φ ∈ construction T hT i`.
  This means either:
  - `φ = δ` where `δ` was added in step `i`, i.e., `φ = decode (i-1)`. In this case, `φ ∈ construction T hT (i-1)` and the condition `∀ Γ : Finset (Formula _), ↑Γ ⊆ construction T hT (i-1) → (Γ.conj ⋏ δ) ➝ ξ ∉ T.theory` was false.
